    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, reduce the heat to medium-high, then add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>baharat</strong> and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1699030425405-x200.jpg",
